String:
- is a non-primitive data type: making String as data type of variable , can store string of text into variable
- is a class providing immutable (not modifiable) representation of sequence characters (everything in string is character)
- based on Unicode character set
- String class is included in java.lang package(no need to import)
    EXKURS:
    ->import statement placed above class header , under package information
    -> import statement used to import class that is from different package
- Two ways to create String object:
    -> String literal
    -> new keyword
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
String Literals:
- String object can be created by using double quote ("")
   e.g. String str = "Hello World";
- String literals are special type of objects -> JVM keeps String literals in the String pool
                                                 => a special memory location for all String literals
                                                    saved in Heap
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
String Pool:
- special memory are in the Heap that stores unique instances of string literals
    -> if we have multiple duplicated String literals in class, only one String literal will be saved in the String pool
        and that String literal in the String pool will be represented by those variables tha are sharing the same
        String of text.
        e.g.
        void method(){
            String str1 = "Java";
            String str2 = "Java";
        }
        ==>> "Java" assigned to both str1, str2, so both are String literals now.
            if you have 2+ String literals with the exact same name and order
            when they are allocated in teh Heap, they will be saved in the String pool because they are String literals.
            String literals do not accept duplicates -> only one will be located in String pool and will be referenced
            by String variables str1, str2. ==>>basically, str1 & str2 are referencing the sae object
    -> String object inside the String pool are also subject to garbage collection when they are no longer referenced
