indexOf() & lastIndexOf()
- indexOf(String str): returns first occurrence of the specific substring
Example:
String str ="Hello World";
sout(str.indexOf("World")); => returns 6, because W of World starts at index 6.
OR
sout(str.indexOf("o")); => 4 (from hello) because it will give me the first o it encounters
- indexOf(String str, int): searches for occurrence of the substring starting from specific position
                            returns index of the first occurrence of substring.
                            -> int determines position of first string you want the index from
Example:
String str ="Hello World";
sout(str.indexOf("o", 5)); =>returns 7, because it start looking for o after index num 5


- lastIndexOf(String str); returns index of last occurrence of specific substring
Example:
String str ="Hello World";
sout(str.lastIndexOf("l")); => returns 9, because this method looks for the last character that was entered ()

  ==> -1 in return means the search for substring is not found
