Substring():

- substring (int beginIndex):
    -> creates a new string that is substring of the original String
    -> starts from beginIndex position to the end of string
- substring (int beginIndex, int endIndex):
    -> creates a new string that is substring of the original String
    -> starts from beginIndex position and ending at endIndex -1(ndIndex not included)
    (e.g. if substring with index until 10 is created only index til 9 will be returned)

EXAMPLE:
String sentence = "I Love Java Programming!";
String languageName1 = sentence.string(7);
sout(languageName1);
=>Output: Java Programming (each gap has its own index)

If I only want a specific part :
String sentence = "I Love Java Programming!";
String languageName2 = sentence.string(7, 11);
sout(languageName2);
=>Output: Java

*sout(sentence) => I Love Java Programming!

