replace()

- replace(charSequence target, charSequence replacement):
    ->replaces all occurrences of a specific substring with another substring
    and returns a new string with replacement
- replaceAll(String regex, String replacement):
    ->replaces all occurrences of a regular expression pattern with a specified replacement String
    and returns new replacement string

    ==>> replace() & replaceAll methods will return the same results
        only difference is replaceAll() includes string regular expressions

-replaceFirst(String regex, String replacement):
    ->replaces the first occurrences of a regular expression pattern with a specified replacement String
        and returns new replacement string
    ==>>only replaces the first matching not all of them unlike the other two above

EXAMPLE:
String str = "I Love Java, Java is cool. ";
String newStr1 = str.replace("Java", "Python");
sout(newString1);
=>Output: I love Python, Python is cool.
//didn't modify anything in object since string object is immutable

String str = "I Love Java, Java is cool. ";
String newStr2 = str.replaceAll("Java", "Python");
sout(newString2);
=>Output: I love Python, Python is cool.
//All Java in entire string will be replaced , still cannot modify string object

String str = "I Love Java, Java is cool. ";
String newStr3 = str.replaceFirst("Java", "Python");
sout(newString3);
=>Output: I love Python, Java is cool.
//this method will only change the first Java not the ones that come after it
